div1.p:
White. Of Mr. Berry, a bacon man in Goswell Street. The Prisoner at the bar seeing this dog went to the door, and locked the door with me in the room. Said I, you shall not make me a Prisoner; then I pressed to get out at the door, and while I was pressing I suppose she took the money out of my pocket, for the young woman who was there, [
Hannah Cutherson
] said, she [the prisoner] has got the money out of your pocket, see whether you miss any thing: then I put my hand into my pocket, and my money was gone; the prisoner had the money in her hand, and I took it from her.
